OL,7,FShe could not walk or talk, and did
OL,8,Fnot know daylight or fresh air, and
OL,9,Fdid not respond to her own name when
OL,10,Fshe was first found, the prosecution
OL,11,Fsaid.
OL,13,FThe mother told police she did not
OL,14,Fknow she had been pregnant until she
OL,15,Fwent into labour, and in a bid to keep
OL,16,Fthe father from knowing she began to
OL,17,Fhide her.
