OL,7,FWhen they went to the home they found
OL,8,Fthe youngster had once again been put
OL,9,Fback into the drawer, and called
OL,10,Fsocial services and the police.
OL,12,FThe woman has now been jailed for
OL,13,Fseven and a half years after she
OL,14,Fadmitted neglecting a child in her own
OL,15,Fhome.
OL,17,FShe pleaded guilty to four counts of
OL,18,Fcausing assault/ill treatment /neglect/
OL,19,Fabandonment of child to cause
OL,20,Funnecessary suffering / injury at an
OL,21,Fearlier hearing.
